                    )</title></titleStmt><sourceDesc><bibl type="frus-volume-id">frus1948v08</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-id">d468</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-number">468</bibl><bibl type="frus-div-subtype">historical-document</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><profileDesc><settingDesc><setting><date notBefore="1948-06-25T19:00:00-05:00" notAfter="1948-06-25T19:00:00-05:00"/></setting></settingDesc></profileDesc></teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-06-25T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-06-25T19:00:00-05:00" n="468" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d468">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.50 Recovery/6–2548: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stuart</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-06-25T20:00:00-04:00">June 25, 1948—8 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>928. Draft note re MFN treatment occupied areas transmitted Deptel 922 June 24
                    should be corrected as follows: Numbered Paragraph 2 revised to read: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“2. The undertaking in point 1, above, will apply on the part of the
                            Government of the United States of America or the Government of China to
                            the merchandise trade of any area referred to therein only for such time
                            and to such extent as such area accords reciprocal most-favored-nation
                            treatment to the merchandise trade of the United States of America or
                            China, respectively.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Marshall</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
